<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="321" type="discussion">
<paragraph box="[235,330,525,550]" pageId="2" pageNumber="321">
<heading box="[235,330,525,550]" fontSize="10" level="4" pageId="2" pageNumber="321" reason="1">remarks</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="321">
There are many descriptions of this species (e.g. Żabka 1985, 1997; Prószyński 1991; Metzner 1999), therefore in this paper it is omitted with reference to those publications. 
<taxonomicName box="[293,423,622,646]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Hasarius" genus.bestMatchDistance="117" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adansoni">
<emphasis box="[293,312,623,646]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="321">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[325,423,622,646]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="321">adansoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a cosmpolitan species occurring in warm climates.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="321" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph box="[235,329,686,710]" pageId="2" pageNumber="321">
<heading box="[235,329,686,710]" fontSize="10" level="4" pageId="2" pageNumber="321" reason="1">habitats</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph box="[235,952,718,743]" pageId="2" pageNumber="321">
<taxonomicName box="[235,365,718,743]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Hasarius" genus.bestMatchDistance="130" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adansoni">
<emphasis box="[235,254,719,743]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="321">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[267,365,718,743]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="321">adansoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occur in various habitats both natural and synantropic.
</paragraph>
<paragraph box="[235,494,751,775]" pageId="2" pageNumber="321">The natural habitats are:</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="321">
- grasslands: Galapagos Islands - pampa, 
<quantity box="[643,706,783,807]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="321" unit="m" value="600.0">600 m</quantity>
a.s.l. (Galiano &amp; Baert 1990), grasses on the Seychelles, 
<quantity box="[385,451,815,839]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="321" unit="m" value="300.0">300 m</quantity>
a.s.l. (WanleSS 1983) and in the China (Żabka 1985),
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="321">
- forests: Seychelles - mangroves (WanleSS 1983), Krakatau - damp forest (Żabka &amp; Nentwig 2000), Nepal - subtropical deciduous forest, 
<quantity box="[749,876,880,903]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.75" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="9.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="321" unit="m" value="975.0" valueMax="1000.0" valueMin="950.0">950-1000 m</quantity>
a.s.l., Bhutan - damp tropical forest, 
<quantity box="[351,468,912,935]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="321" unit="m" value="300.0" valueMax="400.0" valueMin="200.0">200-400 m</quantity>
a.s.l., evergreen deciduous forest, 
<quantity box="[837,980,912,935]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="2" pageNumber="321" unit="m" value="1800.0" valueMax="1900.0" valueMin="1700.0">1700-1900 m</quantity>
a.s.l.,
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="321">- others: Seychelles - beach (WanleSS 1983), Krakatau - waterside vegetation (Żabka &amp; Nentwig 2000).</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="321">The synanthropic are: Galapagos Islands - cultivations (Galiano &amp; Baert 1990), Viet-nam - garden (Żabka 1985).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
